T~L~2700~-1485~0~#000000~~9pt~undefined~undefined~~comment~The RO (Receiver Output) pin of the SP3485 transceiver is the origin point of the receive signal.
 
This signal is connected to pin 2Y of the hex inverter.
 
The corresponding inverter input, 2A, is linked to pin 3Y (labeled LED_RXD) to provide visual indication or signal forwarding.
 
3Y is the output of an inverter whose input is 3A.
 
3A is directly connected to IO23 of the ESP32-C6.
 
Therefore, IO23 is used as the UART RXD pin of the microcontroller, receiving data from the RS-485 bus via two inverter stages.
 
 
The IO22 pin of the ESP32-C6 is designated as the UART TXD pin.
 
This pin is connected to pin 1A of the 74HC04 inverter.
 
The inverter output at 1Y, labeled LED_TXD, provides a signal for status indication and further routing.
 
1Y connects to pin 5A, which is the input to another inverter stage.
 
The corresponding output, pin 5Y, is routed to the DI (Driver Input) pin of the SP3485 transceiver.
 
Thus, the TXD signal from the microcontroller is inverted twice and forwarded to the transceiver for transmission over the RS-485 bus.~1~start~gge56882~0~pinpart
